Citations
Date:  21/3/1868
Source:  Otago Witness
Author:
Vol / Page:  6
Edition:
Quote:  We had a dispute as to the 65 [sheep]. The plaintiff ought to have kept the sheep properly. I wanted to bottle-brand the 65; but he wouldn't consent, and I raddle-marked them. They were counted in my 13,651, but they were not bottle-branded.
